'''Kanazuka Kofun''' (カナヅカ古墳), also known as Hirata Iwaya Kofun, is an ancient Kofun located in {{ill|Asuka, Nara|ja|明日香村}}, Hirata, {{ill|Nara Prefecture|ja|奈良県}}. It is square-shaped and Historic Site1 by the {{ill|Imperial Household Agency|ja|宮内庁}} as an associated tomb of {{ill|Emperor Kinmei|ja|欽明天皇}}'s {{ill|Umemiyama Kofun|ja|梅山古墳}}.

== Overview ==

Situated on the southern edge of the {{ill|Nara Basin|ja|奈良盆地}}, the Kanazuka Kofun was constructed on a flattened area cut into the southern slope of a hill between the {{ill|Umemiyama Kofun|ja|梅山古墳}} (Emperor Kinmei’s tomb) and {{ill|Oni no Manaita and Oni no Senkan|ja|鬼の俎・鬼の雪隠}}. Along the same hill slope, four kofun align east to west: the Umemiyama Kofun, Kanazuka Kofun, Oni-no-Manaita and Oni-no-Sekishoin, and the {{ill|Noguchi Oukou Kofun|ja|野口王墓古墳}} (the joint tomb of {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|ja|Emperor Tenmu|1=Emperor Tenmu}} and {{ill|Empress Jitō|ja|持統天皇}}). 

During the {{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代}}, the stone chamber of Kanazuka Kofun was already exposed. However, the chamber suffered significant destruction in the {{ill|Meiji period|ja|明治時代}}, and from 1995 onward, surveys were conducted to confirm the extent of the site.

